Create a Workload History

A workload history aggregates historical channel data that you specify. When creating an intelligent forecast, it makes predictions based on data in a workload history.

Workforce Engagement is available in Lightning Experience and requires Enterprise, Performance, or Unlimited Editions.

To view, create, and adjust a workload history, the following user permissions are needed: Workforce Engagement Analyst.

When creating a workload history, consider the following:

* There's a one-to-one mapping between each forecast and its workload history.
* If Machine Learning is selected as the forecasting algorithm, your workload history must be at least three times as long as the forecast you want to create.
* The workload history creation flow is optimized for customers who use Omni-Channel queue-based routing.

For Omni-Channel queue-based routing workflows:

* Click App Launcher | Intelligent Forecasts | New.
* Select Omni Workload History.
* Select a queue from the Queue Name dropdown menu.
* Map additional queues to dashboard filter names.
* Select to use all history or filter the data you're bringing in.
* Select a service territory.
* Choose to add to a workload history or create a new one.
* Enter an end date and duration for your workload history, and name it.

For customers who don't use Omni-Channel queue-based routing:

* Click App Launcher | Intelligent Forecasts | New.
* Select the Select my own channel radio button to create a workload history from available channels.
* Select a channel to view history for.
* Select to use all history or filter the data you're bringing in.
* Select a service territory.
* Tell your channel if it's filterable by Skill, Region, or Custom.
* Map these filter names to custom fields created in configuration pre-work.
* Click Next and follow the same steps as for Omni-Channel queue-based routing.
